# unistar-mcp

Go MCP server wrapping `gh` and `git` for PR/CI workflows. Built for small local models: compact tool output, `ERROR: code | …` actionable errors, byte caps on logs.

## MCP tools (use these, not raw gh/git)

When inspecting or acting on a PR or its CI — not when changing this server's code — use the **unistar-mcp** MCP tools. Follow the `pr-ci-triage` skill (`.cursor/skills/pr-ci-triage/SKILL.md`). Do not shell out to `gh pr`, `gh run`, or `git` for triage/backport tasks that the MCP tools cover.

**25 tools** in PR / CI / repo / issue / security groups — see `docs/TOOLS.md` (SSOT) and README § Tools. MCP **Resources**: `github://pull/{owner}/{repo}/{number}/overview`.

Server is registered in `.cursor/mcp.json`. Enable it in **Cursor Settings → Tools & MCP** on first open.

## Common commands

```sh
go build ./...        # compile check
make test             # unit tests (includes doc drift checks)
make verify           # module verification
go run ./cmd          # stdio MCP server
go run ./cmd http     # Streamable HTTP on :8080
go run ./cmd --lazy   # lazy meta-tool mode
```

## Architecture (short)

- `cmd/main.go` → `pkg/commands/` (cobra CLI)
- `pkg/server/` — MCP tools: `server.go`, `registry.go`, `lazy.go`, `exec.go`, `errors.go`, `pr.go`, `pr_chat_tools.go`, `ci.go`, `repo.go`, `issue.go`, `security.go`, `backport.go`
- New tools go through `registry.go` (`[]toolEntry`), never `AddTool` directly
- External commands only via `exec.go` (`run`/`runRetry`/`runEnv`)

Full development guidance: `AGENTS.md` and `CLAUDE.md`.
